http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Novel-way-to-persuade-riders-to-wear-helmets/article14016805.ece

R. Chetan, Superintendent of Police, and the traffic police, adopted a novel way of persuading two-wheeler riders to wear helmets.They offered roses to riders in the city and urged them to wear helmets. They also explained the importance of wearing helmets.Mr. Chetan also flagged off a bike rally by police officers and also members of the public. The participants wore helmets and were holding placards stressing the importance of wearing helmet. “We have been creating awareness among the public by taking out bike rallies in all the taluk headquarters. As the law is already in force, we will also start initiating action against the violators,” he said.